<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 02 at 10:58PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Randall
and southeastern Potter Counties through 1130 PM CDT...
At 1058 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles southwest of Amarillo, moving east at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Amarillo, Canyon, Lake Tanglewood, Mescalero Park and Timbercreek
Canyon.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
